"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is setting both major locator and xticks for the x-axis. When using a date locator, it's generally better to let matplotlib handle the tick locations. Setting xticks manually can override the locator and cause unexpected behavior. Instead, use the locator to set the ticks.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19,20c19\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> fig.autofmt_xdate(rotation=45)\\n\"\n}"